(468, 1, '2017-05-11 05:27:02', '2017-05-11 05:27:02', '<h2>Programmable 15-TAP Hybrid DBNS FIR Filter</h2>\r\nVideo processing filter which performs 5.4 billion multiplications and additions (MAC) per second using Double Base Number System (DBNS). This chip was designed in 2 weeks from the original concept to final tape-out. Implemented on TSMCs 0.35µm CMOS processes with a size of 16mmx9mm (or 144 000 000µm<sup>2</sup>)\r\n\r\nPrimary Designers: Roberto Muscedere and Johanathon Eskritt\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-469\" src=\"http://localhost/RCIM_lab/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/ICDWRBFC.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"446\" height=\"774\" />', 'ICDWRBFC', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'icdwrbfc', '', '', '2017-05-13 16:52:52', '2017-05-13 16:52:52', '', 0, 'http://localhost/RCIM_lab/?p=468', 0, 'post', '', 0),
