(708, 1, '2017-05-11 23:11:43', '2017-05-11 23:11:43', '\n			<h2>&nbsp;Facilities</h2>		\n		<p>The RCIM laboratories are located on the University of Windsor Campus in Essex Hall, room 260.</p><p>Our development platform consists of Sun Microsystems workstations, both UltraSPARC and Intel based. We utilize software from Cadence Design Systems, Synopsys, Mentor Graphics, Xilinx, Altera and Ansoft.</p><p>The test facilities are based on the HP/Agilent VXI-Mainframe system allowing comprehensive design evaluation and debugging.</p>		\n			<h2>&nbsp;Technology</h2>		\n		<p>The Research Centre for Integrated Microsystems currently has access to several different design technologies.</p><ul><li><a href=\"http://localhost/RCIM_lab/complimentary-metal-oxide-semiconductor-cmos-processes.html\">Complimentary Metal Oxide Semiconductor (CMOS) Processes</a></li><li><a href=\"http://localhost/RCIM_lab/bi-polar-transistor-bjt-processes.html\">Bi-Polar Transistor (BJT) Processes</a></li><li><a href=\"http://localhost/RCIM_lab/micro-electromechanical-systems-mems-processes.html\">Micro Electromechanical Systems (MEMS) Processes</a></li></ul><p>All fabrication services are graciously provided by CMC Microsystems.</p>', 'Facilities', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'facilities', '', '', '2017-05-13 08:20:04', '2017-05-13 08:20:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost/RCIM_lab/?page_id=708', 0, 'page', '', 0),
